                     <interp inst="t18261026-209-defend1233" type="age" value="25"></interp>
                  </persName>
             was again indicted for <rs id="t18261026-209-off1157" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18261026-209-off1157" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18261026-209-off1157" type="offenceSubcategory" value="grandLarceny"></interp>
               stealing, on the <rs id="t18261026-209-cd1158" type="crimeDate">14th of September</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18261026-209-off1157 t18261026-209-cd1158"></join>, 6lbs. of soap, value 8s.
            </rs>, the goods of 
               <persName id="t18261026-209-victim1234" type="victimName">
                  Thomas 
                  Birke
               <interp inst="t18261026-209-victim1234" type="surname" value="Birke"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18261026-209-victim1234" type="given" value="Thomas"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18261026-209-victim1234" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18261026-209-off1157 t18261026-209-victim1234"></join>
                  </persName>
            .</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18261026-209-person1235">
                  JOHN 
                  BAIN
               <interp inst="t18261026-209-person1235" type="surname" value="BAIN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18261026-209-person1235" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18261026-209-person1235" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . On the 8th of September I was in the factory, and heard a noise in the loft - no one has any business there; I had shut it an hour before; I called out,"Who is there?" but received no answer - I ran up-stairs, and met the prisoner coming out, with a box lid in his hand - I said, "What do you want? why not take a light?" he said, "A box-lid, to cover a box;" I looked round, and under a box saw two cakes of soap, in another box - I locked up the place, and when Mr. Birke came in the morning I told him; I then put a crooked nail into the soap, and left it there - it had been moved from the cutting-room. On the 14th it was missed, and I went with the officer to the prisoner's house, and saw him find two cakes of soap in his bureau - on cutting it the crooked nail was in it; I told the officer about the nail.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined. Q. Did you state all this to Mr. White, the Magistrate? A. Yes, and he was discharged, because the witness was not there; he was committed by Mr. Hall, at Bow-street. I am not in the habit of calling at his house; Farrell used to call him up in the morning.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18261026-209-person1236">
                  RICHARD 
                  CORFF
               <interp inst="t18261026-209-person1236" type="surname" value="CORFF"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18261026-209-person1236" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18261026-209-person1236" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I apprehended the prisoner - he said he had no soap, and knew nothing of it; I found it in the bureau in his room, and the nail was in it; Bain had said he had put one into it - the bureau was not locked.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. A box of fat stood in the yard; the carpenter sent me for a box lid - I went for it in the dark; the doors were open. Bain called out, "Who is there?" I said, "Me;" the soap had been there for months - Mr. Birke said he had lost none.</p>
               <p>RICHARD CORFF. Mr. Birke said he would not swear to it, but left it to Bain.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18261026-209-verdict1159" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18261026-209-verdict1159" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 25.</p>
